  "limitations": [
    "The derived BSEP count is total cellular BSEP in an average seven-donor reference hepatocyte, not canalicular surface-localized or transport-active BSEP.",
    "No uncertainty was published for the source headline BSEP abundance or total-protein-per-cell value, so the arithmetic result has no defensible propagated interval.",
    "The MRP2 denominator is protein in an isolated human-liver membrane fraction, not total protein per purified hepatocyte.",
    "The MRP2 tissue fraction can include multiple membrane pools and cell types; it cannot be multiplied by the PHH total-protein mass.",
